<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/231</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Reinsch</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram of September 25. If Foreign Office replied as you
                            anticipated you may support it in that attitude. In any event inform it
                            this Government reserves all American rights.</p>
                        <p>Report any further action by Japan.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>